Reasoning: The paper deals with the construction and analysis of estimators for functionals of finite dimensional parameters, specifically for estimating divergences between discrete probability distributions. This falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of polynomial approximations and Taylor expansions, which are common techniques in computational complexity (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of confidence sets and the analysis of sample sizes, which are relevant to statistics (cs.ST).
